ng everything that spawned.<br>
My question is, are the wizards meant to be so rare, and what rate do they drop the heart? From reading posts here I'd been under the impression that it was fairly common, or at least a lot more common then it seemed last night. So just wondering if it was a piece of bad luck, or whether it really is that rare and I should kiss my chances of ever getting the staff goodbye.<br>
And thanks to Glimmerick, Kerenaa, and Ilmarinen of Luclin for spending so much time helping me out on the quest. <br>
<br>
-Therrinn Dawncaller, lvl 32 wiz<br>
Mercenaries of Northshore, Luclin<br>
<br>
p.s. The druid and I dinged, so it wasn't a complete waste of an evening <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 295<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/12/01 11:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of Temperate flux; Heart of Fire</span><hr size=1> There's 2 types of goblin wizards.  Fire (or flame - I forget) goblin wizards, and inferno goblin wizards.  The ones that drop the heart are harder than the ones that don't. I killed the non-heart dropping ones for hours before I realized there was a difference. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
<br>Wizard of the 31st Season
<br>Guild Leader of Nightwatch of Norrath
<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn
<br>Vigor says, 'warriors will hit anything wether its dead or alive.  they are stupid like that' 
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwitek02.showPublicProfile?language=EN>witek02</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/12/01 12:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of Temperate flux; Heart of Fire</span><hr size=1> yup, the inferno ones are the harder ones and they are the ones I was killing, still no drops <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jandellon>Jandellon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/12/01 12:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of Temperate flux; Heart of Fire</span><hr size=1> Well, since I just finished this quest a while back. . . . . it's VERY RARE.  It took me several, several days to get one to drop.  It's off the Inferno Goblin Wizard.  I never could get the one in the bar room to drop, so I was with a high lvl magician, and he got me a little lost, but there is another Inferno that pops some where down a little deeper in a cave area, and that's the one that dropped it for me.  All together, the night that I got it to drop, I was there for about 4 hours I think.  That was with the Magician clearing the whole zone non-stop.  I spent several days doing it though, but that was the longest I stayed in there.  I think it is really just random.  It may drop several times in fifteen minutes, who knows.  I would /ooc and ask to loot it.  There's usually several higher lvl people on my server that are in there for different things, and they don't have a problem letting some one come loot it, because they have no need for it.  Well, that's as much as I know about it.  The Heart of Frost will be easier.  The Heart of Fire is by far, the hardest part of the quest. <p>Janden Furybringer
Lvl 25 Wizard
Metallic Dragons
E'ci</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 300<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/12/01 2:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of Temperate flux; Heart of Fire</span><hr size=1> I got my heart of fire from shouting for looting rights on a dead wizards burning heart.  The heart of frost was MUCH easier for sure. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
<br>Wizard of the 31st Season
